# temp_ocimf_db.csv — SYNTHETIC SAMPLE DATA

This CSV is generator output from `OCIMFDatabase.create_sample_database()` —
**not** the real published OCIMF MEG3/MEG4 coefficient corpus.

- 118 rows
- VLCC class only
- Displacement-axis (legacy; real OCIMF uses WD/T ratio)
- Used for test fixtures and module demos

## For the real corpus, see

- **Digitized lookup tables (master)**:
  `/mnt/ace/acma-codes/OCIMF/OCIMF Coef.xlsx` (17 sheets, Annex A A5-A19)
- **Interactive explorer** (open in browser):
  `docs/domains/charts/phase2/ocimf/ocimf_coefficient_explorer.html`
- **Cross-project lookup prompt**:
  `docs/domains/charts/phase2/ocimf/PROMPT_TEMPLATE.md`
- **Figure PDF extracts**:
  `/mnt/ace/acma-codes/OCIMF/Figures/` and
  `/mnt/ace/acma-projects/B1522/ctr-7/_data/ocimf/`
- **Full standard PDFs**:
  - MEG3 — `/mnt/ace/acma-codes/OCIMF/OCIMF - 2008 - Mooring Equipment Guidelines.pdf`
  - MEG4 — `/mnt/ace/acma-codes/OCIMF (MEG 4)/Mooring Equipment Guidelines - MEG4.pdf`

## Known issues with this synthetic data

- The 2D RBF thin-plate-spline interpolator on this small sample can return
  unphysical extrapolations outside the data hull (e.g., CYw = -3.56 in
  digitalmodel#556 — the real Cyw range from MEG3 Annex A is [-1.165, -0.006]).
- Schema (`vessel_type, displacement, heading, ...`) uses displacement as the
  secondary axis; real OCIMF uses **WD/T ratio (water-depth/draft)**.
- Vessel-class taxonomy is single (VLCC); real MEG3 partitions
  Tanker Loaded / Tanker Ballast 40%T / Gas Carrier Prismatic / Gas Carrier Spherical.

## Replacement path

`OCIMFExcelAdapter` (digitalmodel#563) will ingest the real `OCIMF Coef.xlsx`
and produce a long-form DataFrame the existing `OCIMFDatabase` interpolator can
consume after a small schema adapter — see the prototype parser in
`scripts/python/digitalmodel/ocimf/build_coefficient_explorer.py`.
